01:15.501 --> 01:18.334
["IT'S BEGINNING TO LOOK
A LOT LIKE CHRISTMAS" PLAYING]

01:18.334 --> 01:21.767
<i>* It's beginning to look
A lot like Christmas *</i>

01:21.767 --> 01:24.834
<i>* Everywhere you go *</i>

01:24.834 --> 01:27.100
<i>* Take a look
In the Five-and-Ten *</i>

01:27.100 --> 01:28.701
<i>* Glistening once again *</i>

01:28.701 --> 01:31.367
<i>* With candy canes
And silver lanes aglow *</i>

01:31.367 --> 01:33.968
<i>* It's beginning to look
A lot like Christmas... *</i>

01:33.968 --> 01:36.033
[CAR APPROACHES]

01:36.033 --> 01:37.901
[CAR DOOR SLAMS]

01:37.901 --> 01:39.334
AL:
No!

01:41.167 --> 01:42.868
Daddy's home.

01:42.868 --> 01:44.534
[GROANS]
[GROANS]

01:47.667 --> 01:50.367
I hate Christmas.

01:50.367 --> 01:52.934
The mall was full of nothing
but women and children.

01:52.934 --> 01:56.200
All you hear is,
"I want this. Get me this.

01:56.200 --> 01:57.767
I have to have this."

01:57.767 --> 01:59.334
Then there's the children.

02:02.467 --> 02:04.167
And they're all by my store,

02:04.167 --> 02:06.501
'cause they stuck
the mall Santa right outside,

02:06.501 --> 02:08.501
ringing his stupid bell.

02:08.501 --> 02:09.834
As if you need a bell

02:09.834 --> 02:14.334
to notice a 300-pound alcoholic
in a red suit.

02:14.334 --> 02:16.367
"Ho, ho, ho," all day long.

02:16.367 --> 02:17.501
So, nice as can be,

02:17.501 --> 02:21.000
I go outside
and ask him to shut the hell up.

02:21.000 --> 02:23.634
He takes a swing at me.

02:23.634 --> 02:25.534
So I lay a hook
into his fat belly,

02:25.534 --> 02:27.901
and he goes down.

02:29.167 --> 02:31.400
Beard comes off,
all the kids start crying,

02:31.400 --> 02:32.734
and I'm the bad guy.

02:34.567 --> 02:36.000
Aw, honey,

02:36.000 --> 02:38.634
I know what would
make you feel better,

02:38.634 --> 02:42.767
but I'll never leave you,
not in a million years.

02:42.767 --> 02:45.334
So, Al, what's
the family plan

02:45.334 --> 02:46.968
for Christmas
this year?

02:46.968 --> 02:49.100
Five bowls a-flushing?

02:49.100 --> 02:52.200
Four 'roids
a-throbbing?

02:52.200 --> 02:55.567
Three nose hairs waving?

02:55.567 --> 02:58.167
Two children starving?

02:58.167 --> 03:01.567
* One untouched wife *

03:07.968 --> 03:09.834
I guess this is what
they mean when they say,

03:09.834 --> 03:14.334
"chestnuts roasting
on an open fire."
Eh, guys?

03:16.033 --> 03:17.501
Now, look, I know
last Christmas,

03:17.501 --> 03:18.868
you didn't
get what you wanted.

03:18.868 --> 03:20.501
I saw your
sad little faces.

03:20.501 --> 03:21.901
How?

03:21.901 --> 03:23.467
You weren't even home.

03:23.467 --> 03:25.934
You shot pool
with your friends.

03:25.934 --> 03:29.968
Hey, your faces were
still sad the next day.

03:29.968 --> 03:32.234
But this year, it's
going to be different.

03:32.234 --> 03:35.100
Who here knows what
a Christmas club is?

03:35.100 --> 03:38.567
Oh, isn't that where morons
put money in the bank

03:38.567 --> 03:42.100
to get 2 percent interest
instead of the normal 5?

03:43.801 --> 03:44.901
Uh, yeah.

03:46.834 --> 03:48.167
Anyway, I've got

03:48.167 --> 03:49.734
one of these
Christmas club things,

03:49.734 --> 03:53.434
and was able to save
a pretty penny this year.

03:53.434 --> 03:54.701
So, in addition

03:54.701 --> 03:57.801
to our annual Christmas
feast at Denny's...

04:01.200 --> 04:03.501
This year,
we're getting presents.

04:03.501 --> 04:05.934
Oh, I can't believe it!
Presents! Yes!

04:05.934 --> 04:08.200
Al, this isn't
a joke, is it?

04:08.200 --> 04:10.200
You know, like when
we were dating and you said:

04:10.200 --> 04:13.601
"Stick with me, babe,
I'm really going places"?

04:13.601 --> 04:15.501
Gee, I remember
saying that.

04:15.501 --> 04:18.000
I just didn't think
I said it to you.

04:18.000 --> 04:19.100
Oh, anyway,

04:19.100 --> 04:21.000
Christmas is not
the time for regrets.

04:21.000 --> 04:23.434
That's what
anniversaries are for.

04:23.434 --> 04:24.634
Come on.

04:24.634 --> 04:27.567
Let's all have a little
Christmas "Whoa, Bundy!"

04:27.567 --> 04:30.868
ALL:
Whoa... Bundy!

04:30.868 --> 04:32.601
[DOORBELL RINGS]

04:32.601 --> 04:35.467
That may be carolers.
They may want something.
Bud, hit the lights.

04:35.467 --> 04:37.267
Everybody down.

04:40.701 --> 04:42.467
It's Mr. and Mrs. Rhoades.

04:42.467 --> 04:46.000
Should I fix us up a stink bomb?

04:46.000 --> 04:47.200
No, let them in.

04:47.200 --> 04:48.667
They may
have presents.

04:50.567 --> 04:53.567
Merry Christmas!
Merry Christmas!

04:56.701 --> 04:58.234
Nothing.
Empty-handed.

05:02.067 --> 05:05.067
Okay, who's got
my wedding ring?

05:07.100 --> 05:09.000
Thank you.

05:09.000 --> 05:11.767
Anyway, I just came over
to say Merry Christmas

05:11.767 --> 05:14.334
since I won't be here because
of a previous commitment.

05:14.334 --> 05:16.868
Yes, he's
spending Christmas

05:16.868 --> 05:18.467
with Mommy, you know.

05:18.467 --> 05:21.501
BUNDYS:
Aww.

05:21.501 --> 05:24.634
Why can't you and Mother
get along, Marcie?

05:24.634 --> 05:27.300
The woman hangs
her coat on me.

05:29.968 --> 05:33.033
What about your mother
and her little,
"Oops! Sorry, Stevie.

05:33.033 --> 05:36.801
<i>I didn't know you
were in the shower."</i>

05:39.534 --> 05:41.601
Marcie, you want
some coffee?

05:41.601 --> 05:42.667
Sure.

05:42.667 --> 05:43.734
Hey, I want some coffee.

05:43.734 --> 05:45.067
Oh, I'm sorry, honey.

05:45.067 --> 05:47.400
There's only enough for two.

05:47.400 --> 05:49.400
Kids, you want any?

05:53.067 --> 05:55.334
Why are wives so jealous
of the relationship

05:55.334 --> 05:56.601
between a man
and his mother?

05:56.601 --> 05:58.300
Ah, they see someone
who cares for you,

05:58.300 --> 05:59.300
and it eats them up.

05:59.300 --> 06:00.601
Yep.

06:00.601 --> 06:02.200
My mom even left
Marcie instructions

06:02.200 --> 06:03.567
on how to take care
of me.

06:03.567 --> 06:06.234
Still, one week
after we were married,

06:06.234 --> 06:09.634
guess who was washing
his own hair?

06:09.634 --> 06:11.467
[CAR HORN HONKS]

06:11.467 --> 06:13.267
Oh, that must be
my taxi.

06:13.267 --> 06:15.734
Merry Christmas, honey.
Come give me a kiss.

06:15.734 --> 06:17.467
WOMAN:
Come on, Stevie!

06:17.467 --> 06:19.300
Coming, Mother!

06:19.300 --> 06:22.300
The man's mother
came from Cincinnati

06:22.300 --> 06:23.467
to pick him up?

06:23.467 --> 06:26.968
Boy, if Weenie Town
ever needs a mayor...

06:26.968 --> 06:28.634
Peggy, what am I going to do?

06:28.634 --> 06:30.200
We were supposed to go
to the party

06:30.200 --> 06:31.400
at my bank tomorrow.

06:31.400 --> 06:33.934
I can't go stag.
What will people think?

06:33.934 --> 06:36.300
Marcie, let me
give you some advice.

06:39.334 --> 06:42.601
Don't spend time thinking about
things you don't have:

06:42.601 --> 06:44.434
a good relationship...

06:45.567 --> 06:46.968
nice hair...

06:48.467 --> 06:50.968
a good disposition,
a woman's body...

06:53.534 --> 06:56.167
Think instead
about the things you do have,

06:56.167 --> 06:57.400
and when you do,
let me know,

06:57.400 --> 06:58.834
'cause I've drawn
a total blank.

06:58.834 --> 07:00.234
Merry Christmas!

07:00.234 --> 07:02.334
Al!

07:03.601 --> 07:05.667
Christmas is no time
to make fun of someone

07:05.667 --> 07:08.601
whose life is crumbling down
around them.

07:08.601 --> 07:09.901
Do you know how many people

07:09.901 --> 07:11.934
with lives
a lot better than hers

07:11.934 --> 07:14.434
commit suicide
this time of year?

07:15.801 --> 07:17.968
Now, you should
say something nice to her,

07:17.968 --> 07:20.534
even if you don't mean it.

07:22.434 --> 07:25.634
You look very nice, Marcie.

07:25.634 --> 07:27.400
See?

07:27.400 --> 07:29.901
Now, I'll tell you
what you should do.

07:29.901 --> 07:31.968
You should go
to that party without Steve.

07:31.968 --> 07:34.300
Get wild. Get crazy.

07:34.300 --> 07:36.234
Pretend you're single again.

07:36.234 --> 07:37.834
Dance on the table tops,

07:37.834 --> 07:39.100
chase after men,

07:39.100 --> 07:41.167
rub your red hair
up and down their chests

07:41.167 --> 07:43.033
like a feather-duster,

07:43.033 --> 07:45.133
and then reach out and...

07:51.501 --> 07:54.334
And say, "I'm married,"
and go home.

07:54.334 --> 07:56.167
Like I would.

07:56.167 --> 07:58.534
I guess you're right.

07:58.534 --> 08:01.067
I'll go to the party,
but I won't have any fun.

08:01.067 --> 08:03.434
This will be the worst
Christmas I ever had.

08:03.434 --> 08:05.968
I'll wind up home alone,
sitting in the dark.

08:05.968 --> 08:07.434
That is...

08:07.434 --> 08:09.968
unless some friends
invite me over.

08:14.667 --> 08:16.100
Poor Marcie.

08:16.100 --> 08:18.534
I feel so bad for her.

08:18.534 --> 08:21.534
So, Al, we're really gonna
get presents?

08:21.534 --> 08:23.300
Yes! You betcha!

08:23.300 --> 08:24.934
I pick up the money
tomorrow morning.

08:24.934 --> 08:27.601
This is going to be the greatest
Bundy Christmas ever.

08:27.601 --> 08:29.033
[AL CACKLES]

08:29.033 --> 08:30.901
CAROLERS:
* We wish you
A Merry Christmas *

08:30.901 --> 08:32.000
Hit the lights!

08:32.000 --> 08:33.933
* We wish you
A merry Christmas *

08:33.933 --> 08:35.567
* We wish you
A merry Christmas *

08:35.567 --> 08:37.868
* And a happy
New Year *

08:37.868 --> 08:40.567
GIRL:
We know you're
in there!

08:47.534 --> 08:49.701
PEG:
* Oh, Al... *

08:58.033 --> 09:01.033
Come unwrap
your Christmas present.

09:02.033 --> 09:03.601
Where is it?

09:05.167 --> 09:07.467
It's me, you feeb.

09:07.467 --> 09:09.934
Oh, Peg, how do you expect me
to get excited

09:09.934 --> 09:11.667
when you just rewrap
the same old junk

09:11.667 --> 09:14.133
I didn't play with
the year before?

09:17.334 --> 09:19.133
Oh, come on, Al.

09:19.133 --> 09:21.067
Thrill me
as only you can.

09:21.067 --> 09:24.501
Show Mommy the Christmas
club bankbook.

09:26.033 --> 09:28.701
Okay, but just
this once.

09:35.300 --> 09:37.634
Again, Al, again!

09:37.634 --> 09:38.901
It's never enough,
is it?

09:38.901 --> 09:42.367
Oh, you were fantastic!
Let's cuddle.

09:42.367 --> 09:43.901
Oh!

09:43.901 --> 09:46.701
I suppose a shower's
out of the question, huh?

09:46.701 --> 09:49.501
And I don't think
deodorant is tough enough

09:49.501 --> 09:51.000
to handle this baby.

09:51.000 --> 09:52.934
I'll get the bug spray.

10:07.033 --> 10:08.334
Dad...

10:08.334 --> 10:09.767
I couldn't sleep.

10:09.767 --> 10:12.868
I sense you're on the horns
of a dilemma.

10:12.868 --> 10:14.067
Now, to wit,

10:14.067 --> 10:17.334
you have $280.

10:17.334 --> 10:19.267
But how do you
split it up?

10:19.267 --> 10:20.367
Well...

10:20.367 --> 10:22.567
maybe I can help.

10:22.567 --> 10:26.734
You see, I hate to tell you
this, Dad, but, uh...

10:26.734 --> 10:30.300
Kelly doesn't love you.

10:30.300 --> 10:33.033
Never has, never will.

10:33.033 --> 10:36.067
But you do, don't you, son?

10:36.067 --> 10:39.167
With all
my heart and soul.

10:39.167 --> 10:42.000
But back to Kelly.

10:42.000 --> 10:43.567
Now, how can we
punish her?

10:43.567 --> 10:46.567
How, how, how?

10:47.868 --> 10:49.100
I know.

10:49.100 --> 10:52.467
I bet spending
all the money on me,

10:52.467 --> 10:53.734
and nothing on her,

10:53.734 --> 10:56.167
would fix
her little red wagon.

10:56.167 --> 10:58.033
So remember, Dad.

10:58.033 --> 11:00.501
This year, when
you think Christmas,

11:00.501 --> 11:03.033
think "Bud."

11:12.501 --> 11:13.934
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

11:13.934 --> 11:15.234
Come in, Kelly.

11:16.501 --> 11:18.300
Hi, Daddy.

11:18.300 --> 11:20.667
Um, I just wanted to tell you,

11:20.667 --> 11:23.167
I just got a call
from the doctor, and, um...

11:23.167 --> 11:24.300
I'm dying.

11:26.701 --> 11:29.100
Yep, I've got "bulgaria."

11:33.033 --> 11:36.868
The doctor says
that it's "terminus."

11:38.467 --> 11:41.801
How much time do you have,
pumpkin?

11:41.801 --> 11:44.934
Well, I've got
till Christmas morning,

11:44.934 --> 11:48.000
and the only known cure
is a good present.

11:48.000 --> 11:51.601
You know, in the 250
to 275 price range?

11:51.601 --> 11:55.400
Gee, then I wouldn't have
any money to get Bud anything.

11:55.400 --> 11:56.667
I know...

11:56.667 --> 11:59.267
but it's not like he
loves you or anything.

11:59.267 --> 12:00.767
I mean, when I think
of all the times

12:00.767 --> 12:02.400
that he wished
you dead--

12:02.400 --> 12:04.100
Oh, well, I just wanted
to tell you that,

12:04.100 --> 12:06.567
but whatever you decide
is okay with me.

12:06.567 --> 12:08.567
[COUGHS WEAKLY]

12:10.934 --> 12:12.534
I thought
I'd find you here.

12:12.534 --> 12:13.667
What are you doing?

12:13.667 --> 12:14.701
Loving Daddy.

12:14.701 --> 12:15.901
What are you doing here?

12:15.901 --> 12:18.200
Saying hi to the man
who gave me life

12:18.200 --> 12:19.701
and his name.
Make way!

12:19.701 --> 12:22.300
No! He's my daddy!

12:22.300 --> 12:24.300
What is going on here?

12:24.300 --> 12:26.734
Kelly's trying to pretend
she loves Daddy.

12:26.734 --> 12:29.467
Oh, yeah? Bud's trying to hog
all Daddy's money for himself.

12:29.467 --> 12:30.968
Oh, that's it.

12:30.968 --> 12:32.734
Both of you, out of here.

12:32.734 --> 12:36.267
Daddy is not stupid enough
to believe you really love him.

12:38.133 --> 12:39.868
Now, just stop your whining.

12:39.868 --> 12:41.501
Go on. Get out.

12:41.501 --> 12:43.334
Daddy's getting us all presents.

12:43.334 --> 12:45.100
Go on.

12:45.100 --> 12:46.133
Mwah.

12:52.334 --> 12:53.767
You know, if I were you,

12:53.767 --> 12:57.834
I wouldn't get them
anything...

12:57.834 --> 13:00.501
'cause I'm the only one
who really loves you.

13:02.434 --> 13:04.467
Oh, and by the way, Al.

13:04.467 --> 13:07.334
I just got a call
from the doctor.

13:07.334 --> 13:09.501
I may be dying.

13:11.634 --> 13:14.033
More toaster shakings,
Kel?

13:15.334 --> 13:17.000
Please.

13:24.934 --> 13:25.934
Daddy gone?

13:27.200 --> 13:28.400
Mom, it's noon.

13:28.400 --> 13:30.300
Only noon?

13:30.300 --> 13:33.634
God, I just couldn't sleep
from all the excitement.

13:41.467 --> 13:43.868
Oh, look. I can't even eat.

13:43.868 --> 13:45.200
I'm so excited.

13:45.200 --> 13:46.767
We're getting
Christmas presents,

13:46.767 --> 13:48.567
and on Christmas!

13:49.834 --> 13:52.467
Well, Mom, I hate to put
a damper on the festivities,

13:52.467 --> 13:54.167
but since Dad's getting us
presents,

13:54.167 --> 13:55.534
shouldn't we get him something?

13:56.734 --> 13:58.067
God,

13:58.067 --> 14:00.000
it never occurred to me.

14:00.000 --> 14:03.200
Kind of takes the fun
out of the whole thing.

14:03.200 --> 14:05.267
Well, I'm not spending
any of my money.

14:05.267 --> 14:06.767
I've got expenses.

14:06.767 --> 14:10.334
What, a new shipment of your
favorite perfume come in, Kel?

14:10.334 --> 14:13.000
You know,eau deshore leave?

14:13.734 --> 14:16.000
Go swim in your sheets.

14:16.000 --> 14:20.501
Now, kids, we said all this
at Thanksgiving.

14:20.501 --> 14:23.901
What we've got to do
is get Daddy some presents.

14:23.901 --> 14:25.734
And as my mom always said,

14:25.734 --> 14:29.934
"The best presents
are in Dad's closet."

14:29.934 --> 14:31.567
Well, I'm gonna give Daddy

14:31.567 --> 14:33.334
something
that he's never used before:

14:33.334 --> 14:36.000
his toothbrush.

14:36.000 --> 14:38.501
And I'll get him his underwear.

14:38.501 --> 14:39.834
And as his wife,

14:39.834 --> 14:42.133
he deserves to get
something special from me.

14:42.133 --> 14:44.033
I know.

14:44.033 --> 14:47.033
I'll get him his winter coat
that Buck's been sleeping on.

14:49.067 --> 14:51.601
Oh, this is gonna be
the best Christmas ever!

15:00.133 --> 15:01.801
There he is, kids.

15:01.801 --> 15:04.534
The man
who hit Santa.

15:04.534 --> 15:06.133
Tonight, we'll all
come back

15:06.133 --> 15:07.801
and egg his window.

15:07.801 --> 15:10.634
Yeah, Santa.
Yeah, Santa.

15:13.601 --> 15:16.968
Anytime you want it, fat boy!

15:19.667 --> 15:21.567
The bank! I got to get
to Marcie's bank.

15:25.834 --> 15:27.467
Oh, ma'am, I'm sorry.
We're closed.

15:27.467 --> 15:29.067
See, I got to get
to the bank by 3:00.

15:29.067 --> 15:31.634
We won't be
but a minute.

15:31.634 --> 15:34.300
Hurry up, Mama!

15:49.000 --> 15:52.801
Fourteen ninety-five,
you say?

15:52.801 --> 15:54.200
Yes!

15:54.200 --> 15:55.934
Please hurry!

15:55.934 --> 15:58.434
Mama has the money.

16:02.801 --> 16:04.367
I don't have
any money.

16:04.367 --> 16:05.534
Oh.

16:05.534 --> 16:07.267
Well, who has it?

16:10.834 --> 16:12.133
Mom!

16:14.033 --> 16:15.601
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

16:19.767 --> 16:22.801
["DECK THE HALLS" PLAYING
OVER SPEAKERS]

16:55.667 --> 16:57.667
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

17:50.701 --> 17:52.767
SANTA:
There he is, guys!

17:52.767 --> 17:54.100
No!

18:03.968 --> 18:06.901
Needed some help,
eh, Horowitz?

18:06.901 --> 18:11.234
I guess you're not Santa enough
to face me alone.

18:11.234 --> 18:13.701
Remember, I know
when you're sleeping!

18:13.701 --> 18:17.400
And I know
when you've had beans.

18:29.501 --> 18:34.501
<i>PEG, KELLY & BUD [IN UNISON]:
What did you get us
for Christmas, Daddy?</i>

18:34.501 --> 18:36.968
<i>AL:
Well, family,
the bank was closed.</i>

18:36.968 --> 18:39.601
<i>I have no money for presents.</i>

18:39.601 --> 18:42.000
<i>You still love me, though,
right?</i>

18:42.000 --> 18:47.434
<i>[MACHINE GUN FIRING]</i>

18:53.567 --> 18:55.300
I want toys!

18:55.300 --> 18:56.467
Just a minute,
honey.

18:56.467 --> 18:58.501
Mommy just wants to get
some shoes, okay?

18:58.501 --> 19:00.100
Toys, toys, toys!

19:00.100 --> 19:01.834
Oh, kids. You gotta
love them.

19:01.834 --> 19:02.834
Toys!

19:02.834 --> 19:05.100
Put a cork in it,
demon!

19:05.100 --> 19:07.234
God, what I wouldn't pay

19:07.234 --> 19:08.467
to get rid of him
for an hour

19:08.467 --> 19:09.968
so I could shop in peace.

19:22.534 --> 19:24.968
[HUMMING
"WINTER WONDERLAND"]

19:28.734 --> 19:29.734
Water.

19:29.734 --> 19:32.334
Shut up.

19:32.334 --> 19:36.300
[CONTINUES HUMMING]

19:36.300 --> 19:37.968
You'll never
get away with this.

19:37.968 --> 19:38.968
Oh, won't I?

19:38.968 --> 19:40.067
You be quiet,

19:40.067 --> 19:41.901
or I'll send you
to the bathroom dungeon

19:41.901 --> 19:43.767
like little Bobby.

19:43.767 --> 19:47.634
[CONTINUES HUMMING]

19:47.634 --> 19:50.000
Hey, Bundy, we want
some entertainment.

19:50.000 --> 19:51.868
Okay, I'll tell you
a nice Christmas story.

19:51.868 --> 19:52.934
Gather around Uncle Al.

19:54.534 --> 19:57.100
All right,
that's close enough.

19:57.100 --> 19:59.801
All right, here we go.

19:59.801 --> 20:01.601
<i>'Twas the night
Before Christmas</i>

20:01.601 --> 20:03.400
<i>And all through the house</i>

20:03.400 --> 20:08.300
<i>No food was a-stirring
Not even a mouse</i>

20:08.300 --> 20:11.367
<i>Stockings were hung
'Round Dad's neck like a tie</i>

20:11.367 --> 20:15.067
<i>Along with a note
That said, "Presents or die"</i>

20:16.934 --> 20:19.934
<i>Children were plotting
All night in their beds</i>

20:19.934 --> 20:22.100
<i>While the wife's
Constant whining</i>

20:22.100 --> 20:25.100
<i>Was splitting his head</i>

20:25.100 --> 20:27.868
<i>But Daddy had money this year
In the bank</i>

20:27.868 --> 20:32.601
<i>Then they closed up early
Now Dad's in the tank</i>

20:32.601 --> 20:35.701
<i>Then all of a sudden
Santa appeared</i>

20:35.701 --> 20:39.567
<i>A sneer on his face
Booze in his beard</i>

20:39.567 --> 20:42.400
<i>"Santa," I said
As he laughed merrily</i>

20:42.400 --> 20:45.667
<i>"You do so much for others
Do something for me"</i>

20:45.667 --> 20:47.200
<i>"Bundy," he said</i>

20:47.200 --> 20:49.067
<i>"You only sell shoes</i>

20:49.067 --> 20:52.400
<i>Your son is a sneak thief
Your daughter's a flooze"</i>

20:54.734 --> 20:57.300
<i>"Ho, ho," Santa said
"Should I mention your wife?</i>

20:57.300 --> 21:00.968
<i>Her hair's like an A-bomb
Her nails like a knife"</i>

21:00.968 --> 21:06.067
<i>And he climbs up the chimney
That fat piece of dung</i>

21:06.067 --> 21:08.767
<i>He mooned me two times
He stuck out his tongue</i>

21:08.767 --> 21:14.667
<i>And I heard him exclaim
As he broke wind with glee</i>

21:14.667 --> 21:19.501
<i>"You're married, with children
You'll never be free"</i>

21:25.100 --> 21:27.834
Now, who wants to hear
about the red-headed grinch

21:27.834 --> 21:30.167
that stole Uncle Al's life?

21:30.167 --> 21:32.400
There he is!

21:32.400 --> 21:33.834
He depressed us.

21:33.834 --> 21:36.000
Oh, you beast!

21:40.167 --> 21:42.801
And here's
your money back.

21:42.801 --> 21:45.467
And yours.

21:45.467 --> 21:47.534
And yours.

21:47.534 --> 21:49.234
And yours.

21:49.234 --> 21:51.701
And yours.
Thank you.

21:51.701 --> 21:54.767
Okay, Franklin,
say goodbye to Uncle Al.

21:55.968 --> 21:56.968
[GROANS]

21:56.968 --> 21:58.467
Good boy!

22:00.501 --> 22:03.767
<i>ANNOUNCER [ON LOUDSPEAKER]:
Attention, shoppers.
The mall is now closing</i>

22:03.767 --> 22:05.267
<i>so that our merchants
can get home</i>

22:05.267 --> 22:06.868
<i>and be
with their loving families.</i>

22:06.868 --> 22:08.834
<i>Thank you
for shopping with us.</i>

22:08.834 --> 22:11.834
<i>Merry Christmas,
and good night.</i>

